{"schema_version": 2, "source_hash": "d1fface63b741b8e", "candidate": {"id": "cand-012", "name": "Dr. Nathaniel Brooks", "raw_cv": "DR. NATHANIEL BROOKS\nnate.brooks@email.com | Cambridge, UK\n\nML RESEARCHER / ENGINEER\n\nPROFESSIONAL SUMMARY\nML researcher turned engineer with 5 years of experience in deep learning for perception and robotics. Strong academic background (PhD) combined with production deployment experience. Expert in PyTorch.\n\nEXPERIENCE\n\nResearch Engineer \u2014 ARM Research, Cambridge (2022\u2013present)\n- Developed novel neural architecture search techniques for edge ML inference\n- Published 3 papers at NeurIPS and ICML\n- Built PyTorch-based training infrastructure and MLflow experiment tracking for the research team\n\nPostdoctoral Researcher \u2014 University of Cambridge Computer Lab (2020\u20132022)\n- Research on efficient computer vision architectures\n- Co-supervised 2 PhD students\n\nSKILLS\nPython, PyTorch, JAX, MLflow, ONNX, NumPy, CUDA, LaTeX, Git\n\nEDUCATION\nPhD Machine Learning \u2014 University of Cambridge (2016\u20132020)\nMEng Engineering \u2014 University of Cambridge (2012\u20132016)\n\nRIGHT TO WORK\nBritish citizen", "raw_linkedin": "ML researcher working on efficient inference and neural architecture search at ARM Research. Cambridge-based. Four papers at NeurIPS/ICML. I care about fundamental research \u2014 understanding why things work, not just whether they work. My engineering skills are strong, but I'm most excited about roles that give me time and space for original research. Looking for research engineer or applied researcher roles ideally with academic collaboration or publication goals.", "raw_interview_transcript": "Interviewer: Nathaniel, your background is impressive. What draws you to an applied engineering role at Stratagem?\n\nNathaniel: Honestly, it's a bit of a shift from my current trajectory. I've been in research \u2014 ARM Research and before that a postdoc \u2014 and I'm thinking about what a more applied path looks like. The perception systems work at Stratagem is technically interesting and I'm curious about the defence domain.\n\nInterviewer: The role is primarily engineering rather than research. There's some interesting problem-solving but we don't publish or run long-horizon research programmes. How do you feel about that?\n\nNathaniel: That's a genuine consideration for me. I won't pretend otherwise. I've built my identity around research and publication. I'd want to understand how much intellectual room there is in the role before committing. The engineering work would need to feel technically deep.\n\nInterviewer: It is technically deep, but publication isn't part of it. The 2-days-onsite model \u2014 does that work?\n\nNathaniel: Cambridge works fine, yes. I live in Newnham, I could cycle in.\n\nInterviewer: And security clearance? Do you hold any clearance?\n\nNathaniel: I don't currently hold clearance. I've worked in academia and ARM Research, which isn't classified. I'm aware that clearance would be needed and I'm UK national so presumably eligible, but I'd want to understand the timelines. DV takes a long time.\n\nInterviewer: We can work with SC-eligible candidates and sponsor the DV if needed. Salary?\n\nNathaniel: I'm at \u00a382,000 at ARM. I'd be looking for \u00a385\u201395,000.", "years_experience": 5.0, "skills": ["Python", "PyTorch", "JAX", "MLflow", "ONNX", "NumPy", "CUDA", "LaTeX", "Git", "deep learning", "neural architecture search", "computer vision", "edge ML inference", "production deployment"], "industries": ["artificial intelligence/machine learning", "robotics", "defence/aerospace", "research"], "seniority_level": "senior", "management_experience": true, "education_level": "phd", "career_trajectory": "ascending", "interview_score": 0.78, "culture_fit_score": 0.65, "constraints": [{"id": "fff8a13a", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "Current salary at ARM Research is \u00a382,000", "canonical_key": "salary_current", "value": 82000.0, "operator": "requires", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.99, "currency": "GBP"}, {"id": "2506b70e", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "Seeking minimum salary of \u00a385,000", "canonical_key": "salary_min", "value": 85000.0, "operator": "min", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.95, "currency": "GBP"}, {"id": "7e788f1c", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "Target salary range \u00a385\u201395,000; midpoint preference ~\u00a390,000", "canonical_key": "salary_target", "value": 90000.0, "operator": "prefers", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.88, "currency": "GBP"}, {"id": "225a938e", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "Upper end of salary range \u00a385\u201395,000", "canonical_key": "salary_max", "value": 95000.0, "operator": "max", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.92, "currency": "GBP"}, {"id": "11f8bb5a", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "location", "description": "Based in Cambridge, UK. Prefers Cambridge-based role (can cycle to office)", "canonical_key": "office_location", "value": "Cambridge, UK", "operator": "requires", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.94, "currency": null}, {"id": "bb327914", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "location", "description": "Comfortable with 2 days onsite model", "canonical_key": "office_days_per_week", "value": 2.0, "operator": "prefers", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.9, "currency": null}, {"id": "e50f65be", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "qualifications", "description": "British citizen; right to work in UK confirmed", "canonical_key": "right_to_work_uk", "value": true, "operator": "requires", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.99, "currency": null}, {"id": "d7e316c1", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "clearance", "description": "Security clearance required; candidate is UK national and SC-